sql:
SELECT sector_id, AVG(market_cap) AS AverageMarketCap
FROM firms
GROUP BY sector_id;

SELECT username, last_login_at
FROM users
ORDER BY last_login_at DESC;

SELECT DISTINCT s.sector_id, s.sector_name  
FROM sectors s
INNER JOIN firms f ON s.sector_id = f.sector_id;

SELECT SIN(beta_hml) AS sine_beta_hml
FROM firms
WHERE beta_hml IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
Tech giants: firms in the 'Tech' industry;
Growth in stock value: positive logarithmic return;
Market value: market capitalization;
Tech industry: refers to the 'Tech' industry_name;
Financials or Energy sectors: refers to 'Financials' or 'Energy' sector_name;
Ranking within industry: based on descending market capitalization;
Market capitalization over a billion dollars: market_cap > 1000000000;

sql:
SELECT AVG(market_cap) AS mean_marketcap_mom_over_1
FROM firms
WHERE beta_mom > 1;

SELECT firm_id, beta_hml, beta_mk, beta_mom, beta_smb
FROM firms
WHERE beta_hml > (SELECT AVG(beta_hml) FROM firms);

external_knowledge:
- Financial valuation in this context refers to market capitalization; 
- Sector names and IDs refer to the industry names and IDs; 
- Sectors with higher financial valuation indicate larger average market capitalization.
